ğŸ“– **Description:**
    The `diff2patches` command is used to convert `diff` output into patch files. This helps you save changes in a file or set of files as `.patch` files, which can be used later to update files or share the changes with others.

âš™ï¸ **Options:**
    ğŸ”¹ `diff2patches <file.diff>` --> ğŸ“ Convert a `diff` file to patch files. Each change in the `diff` file is converted into a separate patch file.
    ğŸ”¹ `diff2patches -o <directory> <file.diff>` --> ğŸ“‚ Save the patch files in a specified directory.
    ğŸ”¹ `diff2patches -p <num> <file.diff>` --> âœ‚ï¸ Strip `<num>` leading components from file paths. This helps to shorten the paths of the files in the patch files.

ğŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ diff2patches mychanges.diff

    ğŸ”¹ Converts the `mychanges.diff` file into multiple patch files in the current directory.

    $ diff2patches -o patches mychanges.diff

    ğŸ”¹ Saves the generated patch files in a directory named `patches`.

    $ diff2patches -p 1 mychanges.diff

    ğŸ”¹ Strips 1 component from the beginning of file paths in the patch files. If the path is `a/b/c/file.txt`, it becomes `b/c/file.txt`.

âœ… **Simple Example:**

